# Narrative_Pipeline

## 1. Applies when
Delivery is complex — radio, codex, notice board, cutscenes, environmental
storytelling — or the same fact is delivered through multiple channels.

## 2. This document owns
Delivery channels; UI display rules; notice-board rules; codex unlock rules; radio
rules; cutscene classification; narrative-feedback rules.

## 3. This document does NOT own
World truth; mission body; full dialogue; full collectible entries.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Channels overview · 3. Notice board · 4. Codex · 5. Radio ·
6. Cutscenes · 7. Feedback rules · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Pipeline vs Mission — *how* info is delivered vs *what* the mission is.
- Pipeline vs World — delivery rules vs where content is mounted.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Pipeline defines delivery form, never mission content or world truth.
- Collectible/codex entries live in Collectibles; Pipeline owns only the rules.
